TITLE: Cargarage Map
AUTHOR: Olivier Doorenbos
UNZIPPED FILESIZE: 8.0 MB
DATE RELEASED: October 2006
CREDITS: Map and navigation mesh by Olivier Doorenbos.


MAP DESCRIPTION:
A detailed compact multi-level car park with unique open plan. A bit like a large FY map, its good for fast action rounds as well as slower tactical/camping gameplay. Hostage & Bomb mode combined! (update of "de_cargarage_oli4") Features:
		- Advanced 4 level ELEVATOR !!!
		- LIVE CCTV camera & monitor
		- Four hostages & a bomb site
		- Flooded bottom floor with fish & oil drums - Very dark
		- Button to run lethal electricity through flooded level
		- Buttons to control lights on floors
		- Ambient & damage activated sounds (break the toilets)
		- Optimized visleafs for better frame rate
		- Good Bot nav mesh
		- vmf included!

IMPROVEMENTS:
This is an update of "de_cargarage_oli4" with hostage mode added. The elevator buttons have been fixed! Stairwells now have detailed handrails. Static shadows improvements. CCTV camera can be shot. Fade distances set for props. Elevator doors open instantly on request now. Security room has semi bullet proof windows. Hope you enjoy it!

THE PLOT:
An unused multi-storage car garage in a deprived district appears to be the base of operation of a heavily armed gang who abducted four men a few days ago. An armed force is beeing airdropped on the premises to search it for the hostages and neutralise the gang if necessary. The hostages can be extracted by the helicopter or the conventional garage entrances.

NOTES:
This is the final improved version of my first map. It took just under a month to make the map but that was because I was also learning how to do everything in hammer editor. As there are more than enough normal CSS maps on the internet, I tried to do something a bit different here - an unusual layout etc. I may not be better than all the most skilled mappers out there, but I can at least do something different! I will try to take that approach to the extreme with my next map de_ropax.

Privileges:
You can distribute this map WITH THIS README in any way you want without asking.
You can use the VMF for anything you want as long as you give me part credit.

Hey, I created this a while ago, and finally decided to upload it to fpsbanana.com. Well this map is based in a city environment in a random business. Also this is a beta map, even though there are not any bugs that have been brought to my attention. The main things that are lacking are models and whatnot, and the skybox probably needs to be raised. But other that that is a awesome map in my opinion. YouTube Video: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yvTFI6cYo34

This map started as a mission map for 007 Nightfire. Once it was complete, it occured to me that the layout would be perfect for a hostage map in CSS. So, off I went, completely redoing the textures in high-res with bump mapping. I then set out on a quest to get the most realistic thunderstorm effects possible for source. I stumbled upon a video showcasing the pre-release orange box particle rain. It was by far the most realistic rain I'd ever seen in a video game. The drawback was it's high particle count which contributed to very low frame rates when used in large numbers. I tweaked it down a notch to have a playable frame rate. 

There are multiple routes you can take in this map. CT's spawn in one large section and have two paths they can take to get to the hostages and two inter-connect paths to get between each destination. One path allows them to traverse the ocean and go around to try and sneak in to the ship where the hostages are located, while the other is a large open path that is faster, but will leave you open if you do not find cover. Terrorists have an advantage of height where they can climb atop a crane to snipe the CTs.



Edit: I have converted the map to CSGO and added in changes such as steam coming from the manholes, more props in the streets, less harsh rain and fog (better performance), another path for CT to get to T and vise versa, and a much improved bot navigational mesh. I have not released it yet as I am still trying to figure out how to pack up the map since bspzip no longer works.

Calm Village - Hostage Rescue
by Will2k
will2k@hot-shot.com
http://will8k.tripod.com

Overview
--------
This map is a source remake of my own map cs_calm for counterstrike 1.5

The original goes back to 2003, a date at which I stopped mapping (traveling, lack of time...), and stopped updating the website.

7 years later, the mod/map bug bit me again :) as it did the first time in 1998 and I found myself firing up Hammer and setting it up for CS source.

After spending couple of days on the valve developer wiki to see the new stuff in Hammer/source engine, I figured that the best way to get back to business is to convert one of my own maps from Goldsrc to source, instead of starting a new map from scratch.

I slightly modified the original layout of the map, adding some areas and embellishing existing ones and incorporating the source changes into it.

The result is cs_calm_source; a small to medium map that can fit up to 32 players and that is very true to the original map.

I kept it simple and used existing resources from CSS / HL2. No new textures/materials, no new sounds, no new models.

The gameplay is fast and balanced, the routes are clear and the ambience is not distracting.


Installation
------------
Simply extract the 4 files in the zip archive to your \Counter-Strike Source\cstrike\maps

I have included a nav file for offline play with bots.

Enjoy the map and have fun playing it as I had fun making it


Will2k
